  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. From the graph, the two lines are 2x + y = 8 and x &minus; y = 1, intersecting at (3, 2). Two systems have the same solution set if and only if each equation in one is a nonzero scalar multiple of an equation in the other. Multiplying 2x + y = 8 by 2 gives 4x + 2y = 16, and multiplying x &minus; y = 1 by 2 gives 2x &minus; 2y = 2. Both equations in choice B are scalar multiples of the original equations, so the system in choice B has the same solution (3, 2).</p><p>Choices A, C, and D each alter the constant on one side of an equation without scaling its variable coefficients proportionally, so they do not have the same solution.</p>",
